description:
Content

Too Much Too Young? - Was Davison's Doctor the most 'heroic' of all? Philip MacDonald thinks so

The Fifth Doctor on Television

SEASON 19:

In Production - Ups and downs in Tom Baker's wake. The making of Season 19

The Stories - In which Tegan is possessed, the Doctor plays with fire, Nyssa discovers herself, and Adric eats all the pies

SEASON 20:

In Production - Better the devils you know? The making of Season 20

The Stories - In which the Doctor goes home, Tegan is taken hostage, Nyssa looses her skirt, and Turlough talks to his hand

SEASON 21:

In Production - A lot of good people died. Some of them during the making of Season 21

The Stories - In which Davros is thawed, Chandler is awed, Kamelion is ignored, and Peri comes on board

Further Adventures

The Fifth Doctor on audio - Gary Gillatt cocks an ear to Davison's audio exploits

The Fifth Doctor in books - Matt Michael pores over Doctor Five's novel escapades

The Fifth Doctor in comics - Scott Gray considers the Fifth Doctor's comic strip innings

Afterword by Peter Davison - The Man who was the Fifth Doctor reflects upon his time in the TARDIS
name: The Complete Fifth Doctor

description:
Content

Seasons in the Sun - Is the Third Doctor the daisiest dandy. Or a pompous bore? Philip MacDonald thinks he nose ...

The Third Doctor on Television

SEASON 7:

In Production - Have you heard the one about the eye patch? The making of Season 7

The Stories - In which UNIT takes charge, the Doctor takes a shower, Bessie takes off, and Liz Shaw takes a break

SEASON 8:

In Production - Masterpiece? Or Master disaster? The making of Season 8

The Stories - In which UNIT fights flowers, the Doctor goes to prison, Jo shows her knickers, and Yates fancies a dance

SEASON 9:

In Production - How to meet old friends and hypnotise people. The making of Season 9

The Stories - In whick Daleks attack, Jo gets wooed, the Master watches The Clangers, and Benton wears a nappy

SEASON 10:

In Production - It's my party and I'll cry if I want to! The making of Season 10

The Stories - In which the Brigadier has treble trouble, Jo splits her trousers, UNIT turns green, and the Doctor ends up on the slag heap

SEASON 11:

In Production - While there's life, there's ... Season 11

The Stories - In which the Doctor uses Linx, UNIT battles dinosaurs, Sarah sports spiders, and Yates discovers himself

Further Adventures

The Third Doctor on radio - Gary Gillatt listens in on Pertwee's radio antics (no, not The Navy Lark)

The Third Doctor in books - Matt Michael considers the highs and lows of Doctor Three's novel outings

The Third Doctor in comics - John Ainsworth looks back at the Third Doctor's comic strip antics

Afterword by Katy Manning - The actress who played companion Jo Grant shares her memories with us
name: The Complete Third Doctor

description:
Content

Loving the Alien? - Never judge a book by its cover, quoth Philip MacDonald. And that goes for the Sixth Doctor, too!

The Sixth Doctor on Television

SEASON 21:

In Production - Change, my dears! The making of (the end of) Season 21

The Story - In which Peri is pusillanimous, the new Doctor faces a dilemma, and there's an extraterrestrial kidnap - what I've always feared!

SEASON 22:

In Production - Bigger isn't always better. The making of Season 22

The Stories - In which the Rani enters, Lytton exits, the Doctor sees double, the Sontarans go green and Peri ... well, Peri just sulks a lot

SEASON 23:

In Production - "The Autumn Season on BBC1! Doctor Who returns, only to find he's been put on trial ..." The making of Season 23

The Stories - In which Earth is fried, Peri dies, the Matrix lies, and Mel arrives

Further Adventures

The Sixth Doctor on audio - Dave Owen cocks an ear to Colin's various audio exploits

The Sixth Doctor in books - Matt Michael pores over Doctor Six's novel escapades

The Sixth Doctor in comics - Scott Gray considers the Sixth Doctor's comic strip outings

Afterword by Colin Baker - The man who was the Sixth Doctor reflects upon his turbulent time in the TARDIS
name: The Complete Sixth Doctor

description:
Content

I'm the Urban Spaceman - Cunning or clowning? Philip MacDonald profiles the mysterious Second Doctor ...

The Second Doctor on TV

SEASON 4:

In Production - It's all-change behind the scenes of Doctor Who as a new man takes to the TARDIS. Andrew Pixley chronicles the making of Season Four ...

The Stories - In which the TARDIS crew gets a thorough overhaul, the Cybermen move with the times and the Daleks meet their final end (sort of) ...

SEASON 5:

In Production - Something wicked this way comes. Actually, several somethings ... The making of Season Five - 'The Monster Season'.

The Stories - In which almost every story seems to be set somewhere cold, some furry fiends get a swift sequel and it's bye bye Victoria, hello Zoe ...

SEASON 6:

In Production - A bad time is had by all as the scripts go down the chute followed swiftly by Pat Troughton's morale! The making of Season Six.

The Stories - In which the Cybermen bounce back (again), the Brig arrives and the Doctor's own people finally catch up with him. Did someone mention Time Lords ...?

Further Adventures

Second Doctor Books - Matt Michael considers the highs and lows of Doctor Two's novel outings. Is he really as hard to write for as legend suggests ...?

Second Doctor Comics - John Ainsworth takes a trip back to a simpler time when the Doctor could happily blast away at all and sundry with his trusty laser pistol!

Afterword by Anneke Wills - The actress who played companion Polly shares her memories with us.
name: The Complete Second Doctor

description:
Content

Further Adventures

name: The Complete Eighth Doctor

description:
Forty years since we first entered the TARDIS ...

Forty years since we met a strange old man who whisked us off into space and time ...

Forty years since terrifying creatures drove us behind the sofa ...

Forty years since the birth of a legend ...

For four decades Doctor Who has enthralled millions of children and adults throughout the world. Whether you watched in the monochrome days of the 1960s, or during the colourful 1970s and 1980s, or discovered the all-new adventures of the Doctor on CD and in print during the 1990s and 2000s, we have all been captivated by the Doctor's travels through time and space.

Now, on the eve of his long-awaited return to television, Doctor Who Magazine celebrates the Time Lord's ruby anniversary with a special souvenir edition to honour the very finest that the series has to offer - in all its many and varied forms. With appraisals and fascinating new angles from DWM's finest writers, we're proud to present the perfect birthday present ...
name: We Love Doctor Who: 40th Anniversary

description:
Content

Shapes of Things - Crochety old goat, or cuddly old grandad? Philip MacDonald takes a look back at the original Doctor ... Who?

The First Doctor on Television

SEASON 1:

In Production - Andrew Pixley takes a trip back to 1963, and finds out how a mild curiosity in a junkyard turned into quite a spirit of adventure!

The Stories - In which the TARDIS runs out of mercury, breaks down, is lost in a bet and goes everywhere ... except back to 1963, that is!

SEASON 2:

In Production - The Daleks return again (and again!), as Doctor Who becomes the hottest property on television! Here's how it happened ...

The Stories - In which there are historical hi-jinks, lots of giant insects - and it's "bye!" to Susan, Ian and Barbara, and "hi!" to Vicki and Steven ...

SEASON 3:

In Production - Ratings slide as public interest starts to dwindle and Billy gets bolshy. Can the Daleks save the day this time?

The Stories - In which there's tragedy in Troy, tussles with Taranium, toothache in Tombstone and Trilogic fun with a Toymaker!

SEASON 4:

In Production - It's almost the end for William Hartnell, as the Doctor's old body wears a bit thin - but so does the patience of the production team!

The Stories - In which the Doctor meets smuggling pirates and silver giants, before facing up to the prospect of rejuvenation ...

Further Adventures

First Doctor Books - Matt Michael considers the highs and lows of Doctor One's novel outings.

First Doctor Comics - John (and Gillian) Ainsworth finds out what the Doctor keeps in his magic bag ...

Afterword by Verity Lambert - Doctor Who's first ever producer shares her memories of the series with us.
name: The Complete First Doctor

description:
Content

Golden Years - Brooding bohemian or boggle-eyed bozo? Philip MacDonald profiles the always-baffling Fourth Doctor ...

The Fourth Doctor on TV

SEASON 12:

In Production - It's all-change for Doctor Who as Tom takes the reins and UNIT is left behind. Andrew Pixley looks at the making of Season Twelve ...

The Stories - In which there are wrangles with the Wirrn, struggles with Styre and debates with Davros. But will we ever get back to the beacon?

SEASON 13:

In Production - Season Thirteen - or I'm in a Horror Movie, Get Me Out of Here! Andrew Pixley spotlights the making of Tom's second year at the helm.

The Stories - In which the Doctor and Sarah encounter murderous mummies, crafty Kraals, barmy brain-surgeons and vicious vegetables!

SEASON 14:

In Production - There's no rest for the wicked, as the Doctor Who team pulls out all the stops once again ... a look back at the making of Season Fourteen.

The Stories - In which we are treated to Renaissance runarounds, hypnotic hands, violent Vocs, Chinese crackpots and computers that have gone cuckoo!

SEASON 15:

In Production - The money runs out, a robot dog joins the crew and Tom Baker goes beserk! We take a look at the making of Season Fifteen.

The Stories - In which we meet a rampaging Rutan, a naughty Nucleus, the fearsome Fendahl, a penny-pinching Plutonian and the vanishing Vardans!

Afterword - Producer Philip Hinchcliffe shares his memories of Doctor Who ...
name: The Complete Fourth Doctor; Volume One

description:
Content

Games Without Frontiers - From grinning loon to brooding gloom, Philip MacDonald profiles the final, somewhat schizophrenic years of the Fourth Doctor, in the second part of this fascinating feature.

The Fourth Doctor on TV

SEASON 16:

In Production - Doctor Who the series and Doctor Who the character are given a sense of purpose after 15 years - a quest for the Key to Time ...

The Stories - In which the Doctor is given a new assistant, K9 goes boating, Romana sees double, and the forces of light and darkness pop by for a chat ...

SEASON 17:

In Production - Strikes, inflation and a rather unhappy lead actor lead to a troubled year for the series. But we'll always have Paris ...

The Stories - In which Leonardo works overtime, the Daleks come home, Romana fancies a change, and nobody quite gets to visit Cambridge ...

SEASON 18:

In Production - The new decade brings a new producer, a new look, a new TARDIS and lots of new assistants. But everyone's watching Buck Rogers ...

The Stories - In which Adric joins, Romana leaves, Tegan joins, K9 leaves, Nyssa joins and Tom Baker leaves. Talk about entropy ...

Further Adventures

Fourth Doctor Audios - Gary Gillatt listens in on the Earth's formation, the creation of the Daleks, and a spot of piccolo playing ...

Fourth Doctor Books - Matt Michael runs the gamut from high camp to gothic horror as he considers the Fourth Doctor in novel form ...

Fourth Doctor Comics - Martin Wiggins and David Bailey contemplate the Fourth Doctor's two very different comic incarnations ...
name: The Complete Fourth Doctor; Volume Two

description:
Content

Sign 'O' The Times - Muddling moron, or master of a million chess games? More than just a Time Lord? Mystical magician? Merlin? Philip MacDonald examines the character of the Seventh Doctor ...

The Seventh Doctor on TV

SEASON 24:

In Production - Andrew Pixley finds trouble in the TARDIS, as the colours of the Sixth Doctor are discarded, and we encounter the secretive Seventh ...

The Stories - In which there's Loyhargil on Lakertya, a parasite in paradise, shenanigans at Shangri-La and frostbite at the freezer centre ...

SEASON 25:

In Production - The Doctor celebrated his 25th birthday in 1988, but would anyone notice? Perhaps the Daleks and the Cybermen could save the day?

The Stories - In which there's Terror at Totter's Lane, unhappiness underground, weirdos at Windsor and psychos at the circus ...

SEASON 26:

In Production - It was almost the end of the road for the Doctor and Ace - but first there was some work to do!

The Stories - In which there's commotion in Carbury, husks in the house, bloodsuckers on the beach and pussies in Perivale ...

Further Adventures

Seventh Doctor Audios - Dave Owen listens in to the audio adventures of the Seventh Doctor, Mel, Ace, Bernice and Hex ...

Seventh Doctor Books - Matt Michael discovers what happened after Survival, as he works his way through the New Adventures ...

Seventh Doctor Comics - Jonny Morris leafs through his old DWMs to consider the Seventh Doctor's adventures in the strip ...

Errata - Andrew Pixley puts right what once went wrong!

Afterword - Sophie Aldred reflects on her time on the series ...
name: The Complete Seventh Doctor

description:
HARLEY QUINN, DEADSHOT, KING SHARK and others are a team of death-row Super-Villains recruited by the government to take on missions so dangerous – they’re sheer suicide! After a prison riot at BELLE REVE PENITENTIARY, the hunt for the escaped HARLEY QUINN is on! Collects SUICIDE SQUAD #1-7!

Back Blurb

IRREDEEMABLE. UNCONTROLLABLE. EXPENDABLE.

Who is the Suicide Squad? Supervillains recruited from prisons and sent on covert suicide missions to shave off jail time. Nanite bomb in their necks to keep them on a short leash. Everyone's disposable. Nobody accountable. And brutality and death is just another day at the office.

The Squad's first mission will pit just six --- Deadhsot, Harley Quinn, El Diablo, Voltaic, Black Spider, and King Shark --- against a weaponized horde of 60,000. As their controller, the unflappable Amanda Waller, navigates her band of assassins from mission to mission, a worldwide threat emerges that only they can stop...if these rogues don't kill each other first.

And what could possibly go wrong when Harley finds out that her boyfriend, the Joker, has been skinned alive?

SUICIDE SQUAD: KICKED IN THE TEETH --- collecting issues #1-7 --- is an explosive and daring story that takes you to the edge written by ADAM GLASS (TV'S Supernatural) and illustrated by artists FEDERICO DALLOCCHIO (STARCRAFT), CLAYTON HENRY (ADVENTURE COMICS) and others.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Suicide Squad: Kicked in the Teeth

description: The Blue's fiercest warrior returns as FATHOM: KIANI vol 2 continues! In Volume One, she discovered her true identity. Later, she was labeled a dissident by her own people. Finally, she was killed by Aspen Matthews... Now, Kiani is back-and she's pissed! Kiani learns the fatal cost of her actions after the battle with Thalassar and his forces, as the devastating response from Siphon and the Elite Council is all but a certainty. Meanwhile, Siphon, who until this point had held back in his decision on how to deal with Kiani, decides the only way to deal with the situation, is to confront her directly by force-a risky decision that could topple the very fabric of the Blue's existence in the process if he fails! Brought to you by the creative team of Vince Hernandez, Oliver Nome and John Starr, FATHOM: KIANI vol 2 #3 is a must have for any Fathom fan!
name: The Cost of Sacrifice

description:
This is where it begins! The Evil Max Maximus wants to get to Inner-Earth! He wants the dinosaurs that live there! He wants the powerful DynOre mineral that originates there! SUPER DINOSAUR and DEREK DYNAMO are the only ones who can stop him! The fate of the world rests on the shoulders of a ten year-old kid and his best friend, a nine-foot tall Tyrannosaurus Rex who loves to play video games.

Collects SUPER DINOSAUR #1-5 and SUPER DINOSAUR ORIGIN SPECIAL #1.

Vortigern's Machine tells the story of two 12-year-old friends who, when faced with the problems of their 21st century existence, seek the guidance of their friend and mentor, Mr Vortigern, the owner of a magic slide machine which opens the way into alternative dimensions and mysterious, fantastical worlds! The two friends venture forth into these magical light projections, and encounter many new characters including explorers, hippies, a giant angry gorilla, mystical monks and a troll called Kevin.

volume.name: Vortigern's Machine and the Great Sage of Wisdome

description: Ilsa Daniel is your average world-class ice-skater. She has a loving mother, an overbearing father, and a cold personality that has gained her the nickname of "The Ice Princess." When Ilsa is pushed too far over the edge, "Ice Princess" may turn out to be more than just a nickname... and it may mean trouble for Heidi!

There's been a tragedy at the mall, and it's up to teenage hero Heidi Paige to figure out who's behind it. All signs point to the newly super-powered and slightly deranged ice princess Ilsa Daniel, especially after a strange October blizzard hits Harrington. But is Heidi prepared to stop a girl who's more confused and lonely than she is evil?

Claire, a Quebecoise art dealer, arrives in China to adopt a little girl. There she visits Pierre, her ex-husband, who after fifteen years in China has been absorbed into a life of bicycles, tea, and calligraphy. Claire and Pierre's lover, the young Chinese artist Xiao Ling, become fast friends. Through this classic love triangle, The Blue Dragon looks at aging, cultural confusion, fertility, and creativity, and confronts some of modern China's most intriguing paradoxes.
